  ('a7c8e4db-312e-49ab-b30f-2796f1fad9ec', 'Next Gen Assessment R&D Collaborative with NSEs', NULL, current_timestamp(),
   'Brainstorming', 'Grant', 'A multi‑institutional R&D collaborative focused on advancing next‑generation approaches to assessment, grounded in emerging practice and responsible use of AI. Building on insights from recent field work and early innovation (including new models of AI‑enabled assessment and privacy‑preserving learner support), the collaborative would convene a small set of higher‑education institutions, research organizations, and technical partners to jointly explore, prototype, and evaluate novel assessment models.
Rather than a single exclusive partnership, the collaborative would be intentionally structured as a network to balance power dynamics, accelerate shared learning, and surface diverse perspectives. Core activities could include shared research agendas, rapid pilots, and synthesis of evidence on what works in real educational contexts—particularly where assessments intersect with AI‑driven tools, learner agency, and data stewardship. The goal would be to catalyze innovation while building a common evidence base that can inform the field more broadly.',
   'ai-infra', 'ai-infra-bow2', NULL,
   'ASU, WGU, OpenAI', NULL, NULL,
   NULL, NULL, NULL,
   NULL, NULL,
   NULL, false, false),
