   'INV-099566', true, false),
  ('28dbd68a-0dea-4bc6-8579-0f1f2a88ca59', 'SREE Fellowship Gen Ops', 'Chelsea Koproske', current_timestamp(),
   'Moved to Invest', 'Grant', 'This fellowship program has been sponsored by the LEAD EdFunders Impact Group since 2019. Given ongoing uncertainty around LEAD’s future and the relative strength of the SREE fellowship, this grant is intended to support the decoupling the two and allowing SREE to take full ownership of the program along with managing future funding and sustainability. This one-time Gen Ops grant would cover projected admin fees (about $10K/year) for the next 3–4 years, with some buffer added to support marketing and partial conference attendance, given the recent removal of EdFunders’ amplification support. Intended to provide a meaningful off-ramp of financial support to give SREE the time and runway to plan for future funding and fully take over management of the program.',
   'cross-cutting', 'bow1', NULL,
   'Society for Research on Educational Effectiveness (SREE)', 50000, NULL,
   NULL, 'Q1 (Jan-Mar)', '>2 years',
   'Nicole has been closely involved in shaping this proposed support model as we have pulled back from LEAD group engagement and considered options for future SREE fellowship sustainability.', 'Given Nicole''s engagement, green light to move this investment forward.',
   'INV-099567', true, false),
  ('4dba1c6c-2676-4864-95ed-e6dcaa1e3289', 'Pew Young Generations Survey on AI Perceptions and Use', 'Chelsea Koproske', current_timestamp(),
   'On Hold', 'Grant', 'This grant would support our ability to gather timely longitudinal data from teens, PS students, and young adults around their perceptions, use patterns, and trust in AI tools. This data would serve as a important leading indicator of field impact as well as input shape assumptions and forecasts of adoption, utility, and trust of AI tied to our 2030 Data Goals.',
   'cross-cutting', 'bow1', NULL,
   'Pew Research Center', 2000000, NULL,
   'Currently in conversation with PS and K12 to gauge interest', 'Q2 (Apr-Jun)', '>2 years',
   'Chelsea, this investment is directionally aligned, although I would like to (a) get further along on setting targets and indicators to better understand what type of information is already available and what we will need to gather, and (b) see what kind of co-funding we can generate - before proceeding with requesting proposal. Let''s discuss more in our 1:1', NULL,
   NULL, false, false),
  ('da7dc74d-e711-4f3d-99a3-3d06fe181740', 'Bellwether Learnings on AI Measures & Quality Signals', 'Chelsea Koproske', current_timestamp(),
   'On Hold', 'Grant', '3/3: On hold pending deeper review via the Tyton rescope on data/eval needs. Team will be joining AI day of learning which may surface additional areas of shared interest with other PSTs


The Bellwether team has a full slate of activities planned to learn from organizations do work that could help us refine our assumptions about market demand for stronger AI quality signals + defining quality, including working upstream with solution developers. In partnership with the AI Infrastructure Portfolio, I''d like to explore a potential MLE learning investment to fund specific aspects of the work that can help us to test and inform our specific hypothesis around how to define quality in ways that are technically feasible and resonate with consumers.',
   'cross-cutting', 'bow1', NULL,
   'Bellwether Education Partners', 400000, NULL,
   NULL, 'Q2 (Apr-Jun)', '1 year',
   'Chelsea, let''s discuss in our 1:1: how and when would we use this information? what interest have you seen from the AI Infra team? how would this be relevant to other PSTs that focus on AI-enabled solution development - and would they be interested in contributing funding?', 'C',
   NULL, false, false),
  ('a22fb24c-9520-4dbb-a5a9-44242fb83253', 'MDRC', 'Chelsea Koproske', current_timestamp(),
   'Brainstorming', 'Contract', 'Building the forecasting models tied to our 2030 Data Goals. This is a more narrowly scoped project, and reflects a repackaging of various objectives within the MLE RFP into a few discrete projects to be split bw Tyton and MDRC. Additional refinements to comes regarding the role MDRC may play in in supporting team learning',
