  ('9592ce93-659c-495e-b7eb-c6e12a768e44', 'TX: Supporting District and IHE AI Readiness', 'Julia Bloom-Weltman', current_timestamp(),
   'More Info Needed', 'Grant', '(DAIP Goal 1) Expand on pilot work that was started this year with Dallas stakeholders and consider a thoughtful expansion strategy',
   'sfl', 'sfl-bow2', NULL,
   'Commit', 2000000, 1250000,
   'Potentially other teams at Foundation depending on use case focus and other local funders', 'Q3 (Jul-Sep)', '2 years',
   'Key design considerations to resolve as this concept is further developed include:
1) Primary focus of the investment: Whether the work should emphasize expanding data capabilities through AI (e.g., faster, more comprehensive, and actionable insights), or prioritize specific AI-enabled use cases aligned to PST priorities and near-term decision-making needs.
2) District–IHE coordination: The extent to which the investment should explicitly strengthen alignment across districts and IHEs (e.g., shared standards, governance, or use cases tied to transitions), versus focusing more deeply on one sector.
3) Scalability and replicability: Whether the goal is to deeply support a small number of Texas-based partners or to develop models, tools, or lessons that could be adapted by other regions and states.
4) Amount: I had $4M set asisde for this. I am thinking given all the uncertainty for the above questions, breaking this up into two grants makes the most sense.
5) May consider some collapsing with the next specifically...', NULL,
   NULL, false, false),
  ('4255d98c-78a8-4549-a0e7-050aabb309ed', 'TX: Linkages between the Exchange and Higher Ed: Developing the right infrastructure for true auto enrollment in Texas', 'Julia Bloom-Weltman', current_timestamp(),
   'Moved to Invest', 'Grant', 'DAIP Goal 2: Ensure data governance and technical infrastructure to share data between Exchange districts and THECB is set up',
   'sfl', 'sfl-bow2', NULL,
   'THECB', 300000, NULL,
   'Want to consider whether this would be part of the Pathways envelope potentially.', 'Q2 (Apr-Jun)', '2 years',
   '1) This is directly related to the division-wide prioritized momentum point of enrollment direction in postsecondary. I am confirming with Pathways, but assume this would be no-regrets as part of the state-level enablers as well. 
2) The plan sketches out a few different avenues for automatic enrollment: a) the Exchange (which is the least friction for districts or students), b) side-loading for districts and c) student self report. It will be important in the plan for the pilot year to understand what is possible in terms of how many students they assume will go through the preferable route vs. the other options. 
3) THECB continues to confirm that auto-enrollment is a strategic priority of Commissioner Rossier and Governor Abbott. This does not require deep capacity from THECB members since most of the pilot work will be happening through the Exchange vendor (Education Analytics), but is a useful lens to ensure is addressed in the proposal as well.', NULL,
   'INV-084985', true, false),
