  ('2f5dc726-f30e-4c2d-9cd7-04c15863ffb5', 'WA: Converting unstructured high school course catalogs into structured skills profiles using LLMs', 'Julia Bloom-Weltman', current_timestamp(),
   'Okay to Proceed', 'Grant', 'Priority states and regions demonstrate increased human, technical, governance, and data infrastructure capacity to responsibly test, evaluate, procure and adopt AI-enabled data solutions aligned to student needs, system goals, and guardrails for safety, privacy and equity.',
   'sfl', 'sfl-bow2', NULL,
   'NORC', 550000, 500000,
   'Maybe CSGA?', 'Q3 (Jul-Sep)', '2 years',
   'This investment is crucial because Washington cannot realize a truly connected technical ecosystem for students if one of its most important building blocks, course data, remains locally variable, difficult to compare, and weakly connected to statewide admissions, advising, and research functions. By using AI to extract meaning from course catalogs, the project helps convert fragmented local course records into shared infrastructure for quality, transparency, and action. It strengthens the bridge between K-12 course experiences and postsecondary outcomes, supports more consistent CADR interpretation, and advances WSI’s long-term vision of a modernized, cross-sector data ecosystem that enables timely insights and better decisions for students. If the state can better understand what courses actually are, then digital transcript efforts, advising tools, research access, and regional analyses all become more accurate and more useful.', NULL,
   NULL, false, false),
  ('a12b192c-7744-4063-b9ed-3180691e9c3d', 'CA: C2C Fellows Program', 'Julia Bloom-Weltman', current_timestamp(),
   'Moved to Invest', 'Grant', 'All BOW outcomes could potentially be implicated but this really depends on what area(s) we focus on for the fellows.
- Laying tracks for this in the long term: State and regional systems in priority contexts (TX, WA, CA) routinely produce timely and actionable insights that intermediaries and local district and higher education leaders use to drive continuous improvement in student pathways.
- Impact evaluation focus: Priority states and regions demonstrate increased human, technical, governance, and data infrastructure capacity to responsibly test, evaluate, procure and adopt AI-enabled data solutions aligned to student needs, system goals, and guardrails for safety, privacy and equity.
- Broader part of the strategy for the fellows regardless of the focus areas is to support value proposition of C2C: Priority states establish the policies, funding strategies, and demonstrated value cases necessary for sustained investment in data and AI capacity, including evidence of improved outcomes, ROI, and clear pathways for ongoing state-led resourcing.',
   'sfl', 'sfl-bow2', NULL,
   'California Foundation', 1000000, NULL,
   'ECMC and College Futures are on board. They are reaching out to more funders.', 'Q2 (Apr-Jun)', '2 years',
   'They have a timely ask around their data fellows program- fits across teams and provides capacity to accelerate work that will be sustained by main staff after they build out with fellows.
- Math Pathways: Could fit really nicely but it is currently on hold, where the focus would be on capacity for the secure enclave and ed policy lab pilot
- Pathways priority regions: This is a bit further afield but I have also pitched to sylvia given it would provide impact evaluation capacity, which could be an interesting angle
- EDU-Net: The PET angle could be a useful pilot to inform EDU-NET work. They are completing Some combination of hashing and tokenization,  It is a new way of linking data that doesn’t involve PII.
- AI Infrastructure: impact evaluation for AI solutions (there may be something there)					- CSGA: They are requesting at least 1 fellow on earnings data puzzle- HED and labor economist: credential of value', NULL,
   'INV-105074', true, false),
