  ('45468bd8-b63e-4b43-8c86-41268fc3ea9f', 'CASE Global Ecosystem Physical Infrastructure', 'Marten Roorda', current_timestamp(),
   'Ready for Review', 'Grant', 'At ACT, I kicked off the first version of CASE Network back in 2019 as a $300,000 key sponsor. 1Edtech recently sent me a concept note for a requested investment in the CASE Global Ecosystem (CGE). CGE is the next evolution of the CASE Network 2—and a decisive shift in approach. CGE is a federated, open, globally governed public infrastructure for learning frameworks. It allows states, institutions, sector bodies, and international authorities to host and govern their own standards and competencies locally, while participating in a synchronized global trust network that ensures interoperability, provenance, and long-term durability.
Philanthropy plays a catalytic role, funding the creation of shared public infrastructure that the market will not build on its own—while avoiding perpetual dependency. By the end of this arc, CGE operates as a self-sustaining global public utility: open, resilient, and governed in the public interest. It becomes foundational infrastructure for learner mobility, education-to-employment pathways, and workforce alignment—ensuring that the backbone of learning and skills systems remains interoperable, equitable, and publicly stewarded for decades to come.
What CGE Enables:
•	A public, open alternative to proprietary skills frameworks
•	Seamless mobility for learners across states, systems, and borders   
•	Reliable, high-quality mappings between frameworks and competencies
•	Regionally hosted but globally discoverable standards
•	Efficient integration for publishers, curriculum tools, platforms, and employers
•	A foundation for skills-based hiring, credit transfer, and lifelong learning.
As part of a total request of $13.5M over 5 years, the Gates Foundation would be a co-funder, contributing $1M for the first two years of the plan: Bootstrap MVP, build the core federated infrastructure (year 1); expand and govern, operationalize, onboard, and formalize trust (year 2). Our contribution would focus on building and operationalizing the actual physical infrastructure in a way that is complementary to and aligned with the EDUcore project.',
   'ai-infra', 'ai-infra-bow1', NULL,
   '1Edtech', 1000000, 300000,
   NULL, 'Q2 (Apr-Jun)', '2 years',
   NULL, NULL,
   NULL, false, false),
  ('21399ad0-357d-41e0-a3dc-4b0685579f63', 'Credentials registry and CTDL extension to the AI enabling infrastructure', 'Marten Roorda', current_timestamp(),
   'Ready for Review', 'Grant', 'While EDUcore will recombine the CTDL language and CTDL xTRA AI-powered tool with its CEDS ontology foundation, there is a need to further support this focused, high-leverage subset of infrastructure to make education and workforce data more transparent, interoperable, and AI-ready. The grant would advance Credential Engine’s CTDL xTRA capability to help convert fragmented public information about credentials, skills, pathways, and outcomes into structured, machine-readable data that can be validated, linked, and reused across systems. It would also support adoption and scaling of Credential Engine to become the source of truth for all national credentials. The grant would indirectly support other Gates Foundation investments, including EDUcore and the CEDS Ontology, by strengthening the shared semantic and technical foundation required for more effective, equitable, and reusable education-to-work data infrastructure.',
   'ai-infra', 'ai-infra-bow1', NULL,
   'Credential Engine', 1000000, 300000,
   NULL, 'Q2 (Apr-Jun)', '2 years',
   NULL, NULL,
   NULL, false, false),
  ('8dbf3338-0f86-40a1-a49e-9359f13d60b3', 'AI Safety and Guardrails Consumer Reports', 'Marten Roorda', current_timestamp(),
   'Ready for Review', 'Grant', 'The huge potential benefits of daily student AI learning and tutoring are matched by massive risks.  Learners, parents, and educators all want to know if AI is both safe and effective.  The time to act to create safety and efficacy assurances for minors is now. Government AI controls only become bipartisan when focused on minors, but could become applicable for all ages opt in. 
EDU and FullScale will focus on enabling AI solutions, generating evidence, and improving system feedback loops.  We will convene two panels of experts to create and oversee a framework that evaluates evidence from providers of the safety and efficacy of their AI tools and tutors.  We will convene a national summit.  In January 2027 we will publish the first “consumer reports” of safe and effective AI learning.  District and family consumers and state regulators can use these reports to preference or restrict technologies.',
   'sfl', 'ai-infra-bow2', NULL,
   'EDU', 4000000, 1000000,
   NULL, 'Q3 (Jul-Sep)', '2 years',
   NULL, NULL,
   NULL, false, false),
  ('696db254-2154-4016-9be2-ee88b5ca055d', 'ADL and ELR Salvage with I2IDL as a Vertical Extension of the EDUcore ecosystem', 'Marten Roorda', current_timestamp(),
   'Ready for Review', 'Grant', 'Sudden closure of DoD’s ADL Initiative creates an urgent window to rescue decades of learning technology assets, innovations and institutional knowledge, and an opportunity to broaden impact across education. Former ADL team members with the non-profit I2IDL and CEDS team. Mission: 1. Migrate essential ADL infrastructure into public goods in year one. 2. Formalize the ADL-drafted Enterprise Learner Record (ELR) to use CEDS and T3 Network LER spec, and HR Open JEDx specifications into payload-agnostic international IEEE standards with further development, hosting and support in years 2-3. These unify with other standards as a secure, cross-platform foundation for portable AI learner memory. This investment will be part of the bigger picture of EDUcore that will include extension into specific verticals like, in this case, the military. We can make sure that the investment is fully aligned with EDUcore',
   'ai-infra', 'ai-infra-bow1', NULL,
   'EDU/I2IDL', 1000000, 350000,
   NULL, 'Q3 (Jul-Sep)', '2 years',
   NULL, NULL,
   NULL, false, false),
