  ('dcf2f4e4-7adb-4752-8ab4-9371a53a8a00', 'Sustainable Evaluation Infrastructure in Wayfinding and Learning', 'Pavani Reddy', current_timestamp(),
   'Moved to Invest', 'Bucket (multiple investments)', 'Hi!  The objective of this investment is to support the development of a sustainable evaluation infrastructure in Wayfinding and Learning through catalyzing the development of a vertical division inside of Humane-Intelligence Public Benefit Corporation, such that independent affordable evaluation of all AI features introduced to wayfinders and learners can occur and serve the ecosystem.  The justification for this anchor investment in the BOW: AI Evaluation Technologies & Evidence Acceleration (in Wayfinding and Learning) is that evaluation infrastructure - as much as we have high hopes for agentic AI - is not going to build and sustain itself in the education ecosystem.  Without deep grounding in the field of AI evaluation coupled with bleeding edge experimentation by those experienced and skilled in AI evaluation, the work would lack relevance, broad adoption, trust and sustainability.',
   'ai-infra', 'ai-infra-bow2', NULL,
   'Humane-Intelligence Public Benefit Corporation', 10000000, NULL,
   'While $10M would need to be from Gates Foundation to participate in Humanity AI, other funders at the table include Omidyar Network and a dozen other philanthropies as well as private investors.  Goal is for total raise to be about $25M achieved by EOY', 'Q1 (Jan-Mar)', '>2 years',
   'To elaborate on the Idea Type, this investment is a portfolio of investments to cover serving stakeholders who would develop and use evaluations (solution-builders, independent evaluators, buyers, buyer influencers, investors, civil society, and policymakers).  E.g. We are also drawing specific connection with current consortia investment for K12''s Digital Promise, separately with Communities in Schools due to its focus in high poverty communities, and broad access higher education intermediaries with input from Postsecondary Success.  My personal goal is to catalyze this vertical to secure an operating budget of ~$5M per year, while recurring revenue is built through this effort and outside this effort by the the corporation, so that the $10M from Gates Foundation to get this going is the total and final amount for this anchor.', 'Wanted to clarify to support the process and Allan as approver, that this core investment entails a major communication dimension (is being built in collaboration with Libby and Chapin, including a global angle related to "human flourishing"), an MOU with Humanity AI and encompassed partnership with Common Sense Media''s Youth and Safety Institute.',
   'INV-098001', true, false),
  ('f2c46ca1-f311-4f8d-9121-70f70f45f8f0', 'Gallup study of Gen Z and their parents on using AI (flourishing, wellbeing, etc.)', 'Pavani Reddy', current_timestamp(),
   'Moved to Invest', 'Grant', 'With support from the Walton Family Foundation, the Gallup organization has already created the Gen Z panel for studies across socioeconomic groups on Gen Z and their parents opinions about using AI.  The request is made by Angela Duckworth and her team for incremental dollars for additional phases, enabling the team to analyze changes in AI use as they predict changes in outcomes in cross-panel lagged analyses.  The investment would help us incorporate student and parent voice as well as become better informed about widespread perceptions per the attached prompts.',
   'ai-infra', 'ai-infra-bow2', NULL,
   'Angela Duckworth''s team and/or Gallup, not sure', 160000, NULL,
   'Walton', 'Q1 (Jan-Mar)', '1 year',
   'Matt has opined that this could be no regrets given that it could inform us about priority areas: tutoring/advising- and I am influencing the question set given that it seems slightly narrow toward the “solo” nature of how the public thinks of AI through the quintessential product feature of a “chatbot” – I wanted to interject a question about AI supporting collaboration in a way that could or does improve how humans relate to one another.  We are working on that...(last year, Vic and I learned more about this as we both know Angela from our past work and Vic supports student voice, as well, as a useful input into our work).', NULL,
