  ('c5142a1e-5620-4c95-8477-8f4889134998', 'Humanity AI Pooled Fund', 'Pavani Reddy', current_timestamp(),
   'Moved to Invest', 'Grant', 'Humanity AI is a cross-sector initiative governed by a Steering Committee comprised of representatives from prominent philanthropic institutions, including the Omidyar Network, MacArthur Foundation, Mozilla Foundation, Ford Foundation, Mellon Foundation, and others. The initiative funds projects aligned with its mission to ensure that AI development and adoption is equitable, human-centered, and beneficial to society. Contributions are pooled and deployed collectively to support high-impact projects selected through a collaborative grantmaking process.  This opportunity aligns with the Gates Foundation''s U.S. Program strategy across two key verticals:
Education
AI is rapidly reshaping learning environments, teaching practices, and educational access. Humanity AI–funded projects in this vertical may address:

Equitable access to AI-powered learning tools for historically underserved students
Support for educators navigating AI integration in K–12 and postsecondary settings
Development of AI literacy frameworks and curricula
Risks of algorithmic bias in admissions, assessment, and credentialing systems

Talent & Economy
The intersection of AI and the workforce presents both significant opportunity and risk, particularly for workers in low-wage, high-disruption sectors. Projects in this vertical may address:

Workforce transitions and reskilling in the context of AI-driven automation
Equitable access to AI-enabled economic opportunity
Responsible AI use by employers in hiring, performance management, and job design
Policy frameworks that protect workers while enabling innovation',
   'hub', 'hub-bow1', NULL,
   'Rockefeller Philanthropy Advisors', 1000000, 200000,
   'Omidyar Network | MacArthur | Kapor Center | GitLab Foundation | Mozilla Foundation | Packard Foundation | Lumina Foundation | Ford Foundation | Mellon Foundation | Siegel Endowment | Doris Duke Foundation', 'Q2 (Apr-Jun)', '>2 years',
   'This would be $200k per year over 5 years', 'From 3/18 AI Infr. Portfolio meeting, Matt said okay to proceed and asked Pavani to seek out add''l funding from Comms',
   'INV-105345', true, false),
  ('c22e1c21-84be-467d-846d-a7dc29bc590a', 'AI Eval Infrastructure Ecosystem Mapping', 'Pavani Reddy', current_timestamp(),
