  ('bce6259d-40e0-4b6f-a60e-17ec3891e630', 'Establish pro-social outcomes/benchmarks for HITL for AI improvement, Phase 0', 'Vic Vuchic', current_timestamp(),
   'Brainstorming', 'Grant', 'The Communications team received feedback that our 2030 goals lack human centricity.  In addition, there are concerns both internally and in the field that AI will further isolate people and learners as products have incentives to in essence, addict them and maximize time on product.  The term and concept of Pro-Social AI has emerged as a goal, that is, AI that actually facilitates and increases connection, relationships and social capital, but it lacks definition, clarity on "what good looks like", and understanding of how you incentivize or drive more pro-social AI products.  AI will optimize relentlessly towards whatever target outcome it is pointed to, and current products largely target isolated learning processes or outcomes.  If we can incorporate goals of peer to peer and learner to educator/counselor outcomes as targets for AI, it should be able to improve connection and human relation as opposed to isolate learners.  This grant will be to the Christensen Institute to support the leader in the space, Julia Freeland Fisher, to take a draft framework for Pro-Social AI, iterate on it, landscape actors in the space, and identify strategic leverage points and approaches to begin to build a bigger signal and incentive for Pro-Social AI in the education and advising sectors.',
   'ai-infra', 'ai-infra-bow2', NULL,
   'Clayton Christiansen Institute or Rhithm Project', 500000, 300000,
   'K12, PS', 'Q3 (Jul-Sep)', '1 year',
   'This would queue up a much larger data and benchmark/eval effort.
Potential for MLE to tag along.  Draft Framework here: https://bmgf-my.sharepoint.com/:w:/r/personal/vic_vuchic_gatesfoundation_org/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7BDD4DC963-B48E-4959-ACD1-B0452F5BABDB%7D&file=Pro%20Social%20AI%20Eval.docx&action=default&mobileredirect=true&wdOrigin=OUTLOOK-METAOS.FILEBROWSER', NULL,
   NULL, false, false),
